==English==

===Etymology===
Alteration of ''yes sir''.

===Exclamation===
'''yessir'''
# (''Informal'') Expressing [[assent]], especially to a superior.

==Wikipedia dump==
Yessir is a very popular [[slang]] term on the [[Isle of Man]].  It is commonly used at the end of the sentence for reassurance.  The phrase could mean something like 'isn't it?', 'you know' or simply 'friend'.  Some believe the term originates from [[Swedish language|Swedish]] and [[Danish language|Danish]] (yassoo) where it is used in a similar manner.